    {"back": "<b>Answer: A) 0.25</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>To be delayed over three minutes, either the car or the bus must arrive between 7:20 and 7:22.<br>The probability for each is 2/15. The probability they both arrive in that interval is (2/15)(2/15).<br>Thus, the probability of at least one being delayed is 2/15 + 2/15 \u2013 (2/15)(2/15) = 56/225 = 0.25.<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q237. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "A car and a bus arrive at a railroad crossing at times independently and uniformly<br>distributed between 7:15 and 7:30. A train arrives at the crossing at 7:20 and halts traffic<br>at the crossing for five minutes.<br><br>Calculate the probability that the waiting time of the car or the bus at the crossing<br>exceeds three minutes.<br><br>A) 0.25<br>B) 0.27<br>C) 0.36<br>D) 0.40<br>E) 0.56", "tags": ["ExamP::UnivariateRV", "ExamP::UnivariateRV::ContinuousDistributions"]},
