    {"back": "<b>Answer: D) 1,150,000</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>Let X denote the number of deaths next year, and S denote life insurance payments next year.<br>Then S = 50,000X, where X ~ Bin(1000, 0.014). Therefore,<br>2<br>( ) (50,000 ) 50,000(1000)(0.014) 700,000<br>( ) (50,000 ) 50,000 (1000)(0.014)(0.986) 34,510,000,000<br>( ) 185,769.<br>ES E X<br>Var S Var X<br>StdDev S<br>= = =<br>= = =<br>=<br><br>The 99th percentile is 700,000+185,769(2.326)= 1,132,099, which rounds to 1,150,000.<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q240. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "A company provides a death benefit of 50,000 for each of its 1000 employees. There is a<br>1.4% chance that any one employee will die next year, independent of all other<br>employees. The company establishes a fund such that the probability is at least 0.99 that<br>the fund will cover next year\u2019s death benefits.<br><br>Calculate, using the Central Limit Theorem, the smallest amount of money, rounded to<br>the nearest 50 thousand, that the company must put into the fund.<br><br>A) 750,000<br>B) 850,000<br>C) 1,050,000<br>D) 1,150,000<br>E) 1,400,000", "tags": ["ExamP::MultivariateRV", "ExamP::MultivariateRV::SumsAndCLT"]},
