    {"back": "<b>Answer: A) 0.20</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>W \u2013 T has a normal distribution with mean 0 and variance 4 + 12 = 16.<br>( ) 1 ( 1 1)<br>( 1 (0,16) 1) ( .25 (0,1) .25) 0.197<br>PWT P WT<br>PN P N<br>\u2212 &lt; = \u2212&lt; \u2212 &lt;<br>= \u2212&lt; &lt; = \u2212 &lt; &lt; =<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q345. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "An actuary wishes to predict the size W of a claim using a predictor T. Suppose that W<br>and T are independent and normally distributed with the same mean and with variances 4<br>and 12, respectively.<br><br>Calculate [| | 1].PW T\u2212&lt;<br><br>A) 0.20<br>B) 0.23<br>C) 0.38<br>D) 0.60<br>E) 0.68", "tags": ["ExamP::UnivariateRV", "ExamP::UnivariateRV::ContinuousDistributions"]},
    {"back": "<b>Answer: B) 0.46</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>The only way exactly two of the events can occur is if A and B both occur. Hence<br>[ ] 0.06.PA B\u2229=<br>Because the intersections of A and C and of B and C are empty,<br>0.90 [ ] [ ] [ ] [ ] [ ].PA B C PA PB PC PA B= \u222a\u222a = + + \u2212 \u2229<br>The probability of exactly one of A and B is [ ] [ ] 2 [ ] 0.38.PA PB PA B+ \u2212 \u2229=<br>Therefore, [ ] [ ] [ ] 0.38 0.06 0.44.PA PB PA B+ \u2212 \u2229= + =<br>Then, P[C] = 0.90 \u2013 0.44 = 0.46.<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q346. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "A, B, and C are three events defined on the same sample space. A and C are mutually<br>exclusive and B and C are mutually exclusive. The probability that at least one of the<br>three events occurs is 0.90. The probability that exactly two of the three events occur is<br>0.06. The probability that exactly one of the events A or B occurs is 0.38.<br><br>Calculate P[C].<br><br>A) 0.32<br>B) 0.46<br>C) 0.52<br>D) 0.56<br>E) 0.58", "tags": ["ExamP::GeneralProbability", "ExamP::GeneralProbability::SampleSpacesEvents"]},
    {"back": "<b>Answer: D) 3.18</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>22 2<br>2<br>0.91, 0() 0.09, 1<br>( ) (0)(0.91) (1)(0.09) 0.09<br>( ) (0 )(0.91) (1 )(0.09) 0.09<br>( ) 0.09 0.09 0.0819<br>( ) 0.0819 0.28618<br>0.28618( ) 3.179797.09<br>ypy y<br>EY<br>EY<br>VY<br>SD Y<br>CV Y<br>=\uf8f1=\uf8f2 =\uf8f3<br>=+=<br>=+=<br>= \u2212=<br>= =<br>= =<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q347. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "Let X = 1 if termites are present in a building and X = 0 if they are not.<br>Let Y = 1 if a test indicates the presence of termites in that building and Y = 0 if it does<br>not.<br>The joint probabilities of X and Y are:<br><br>P[X=0, Y=0] = 0.90<br>P[X=1, Y=0] = 0.01<br>P[X=0, Y=1] = 0.05<br>P[X=1, Y=1] = 0.04<br><br>Calculate the coefficient of variation for Y.<br><br>A) 0.31<br>B) 0.91<br>C) 0.95<br>D) 3.18<br>E) 4.36", "tags": ["ExamP::MultivariateRV", "ExamP::MultivariateRV::JointDistributions"]},
    {"back": "<b>Answer: E) 0.973</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>The policyholder will receive benefits if and only if at least 1 of the 3 losses exceeds 30.<br>The probability that a given loss exceeds 30 is (100 - 30)/100 = 0.7.<br><br>The probability that no losses exceed 30 is<br>3(1 0.7) 0.027.\u2212=<br>The probability that at least one loss exceeds 30 is 1 \u2013 0.027 = 0.973.<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q348. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "A policyholder incurs one loss under each of three policies. Each policy has a deductible<br>of 30. Losses under each policy are uniformly distributed on the interval [0, 100].<br><br>The three losses are mutually independent.<br><br>Calculate the probability that the policyholder will receive benefits from any of the three<br>policies.<br><br>A) 0.027<br>B) 0.343<br>C) 0.657<br>D) 0.700<br>E) 0.973", "tags": ["ExamP::GeneralProbability", "ExamP::GeneralProbability::Independence"]},
