    {"back": "<b>Answer: D) 200</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>21 1<br>100<br>100<br>21 1<br>100<br>100<br>1 100 100<br>0.5 100 100 1 100 200<br>M M<br>c x dx cx c c<br>x dx x M M<br>\u221e \u221e\u2212\u2212 \u2212<br>\u2212\u2212 \u2212<br>= = \u2212 = \u21d2=<br>= = \u2212 = \u2212 \u21d2=<br>\u222b<br>\u222b<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q395. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "An insurer\u2019s losses are modeled by a random variable X, with density function, f, where<br>f(x) is proportional to 2<br>1<br>x<br>, for x &gt; 100, and 0, otherwise.<br><br>Calculate the median of X.<br><br>A) 100<br>B) 120<br>C) 150<br>D) 200<br>E) 300", "tags": ["ExamP::UnivariateRV", "ExamP::UnivariateRV::ContinuousDistributions"]},
