    {"back": "<b>Answer: B) 0.369</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>Let<br>= working lifetime of chips, in years. Then<br>/7.2<br>/7.2<br>0.05 [ ] 1<br>0.95<br>/ 7.2 0.05129<br>0.3693<br>t<br>t<br>PX t e<br>e<br>t<br>t<br>\u2212<br>\u2212<br>= \u2264= \u2212<br>=<br>\u2212= \u2212<br>=<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q428. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "The working lifetime of a master computer chip that regulates the electronic components<br>of an automobile engine is exponentially distributed with a mean of 7.2 years. Under a<br>warranty, the chip manufacturer will replace any chip that fails within t years. It is<br>expected that 5% of all chips will be replaced under this warranty.<br><br>Calculate t.<br><br>A) 0.007<br>B) 0.369<br>C) 0.416<br>D) 0.501<br>E) 0.720", "tags": ["ExamP::UnivariateRV", "ExamP::UnivariateRV::ContinuousDistributions"]},
