    {"back": "<b>Answer: B) 11/108</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>The solution is the sum of (y/x)p(x,y) over the six combinations of x and y. Because the three<br>cases where y = 0 contribute nothing to the total, the solution is<br><br>(1/1)(1/18) + (1/2)(1/18) + (1/3)(1/18) = (6 + 3 + 2)/108 = 11/108.<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q467. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "Within a fleet of aircraft, planes are subject to mechanical inspection. For a randomly<br>selected airplane, let X denote the number of inspections in the past year and Y the<br>number of repairs. The joint probability function of X and Y is given by<br><br>23 , for 1, 2,3 and 0,1(, ) 18<br>0, other wise.<br>x y xy xypxy<br>\u2212\u2212+\uf8f1 = =\uf8f4=\uf8f2<br>\uf8f4\uf8f3<br><br>Calculate the expected number of repairs per inspection, E Y<br>X<br>\uf8eb\uf8f6<br>\uf8ec\uf8f7\uf8ed\uf8f8<br>.<br><br>A) 3/38<br>B) 11/108<br>C) 11/36<br>D) 1/2<br>E) 11/18", "tags": ["ExamP::MultivariateRV", "ExamP::MultivariateRV::JointDistributions"]},
