    {"back": "<b>Answer: C) 2.25</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>Let X represent the number of accident-free employees; X is binomially distributed.<br>Let n = number of employees = 12.<br>Let p = the probability that a given employee is accident-free this year.<br>9 = E(X) = np = 12p, so p = 0.75.<br>Var(X) = np(1 \u2013 p) = 9(1 \u2013 0.75) = 2.25.<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q494. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "Each of the twelve employees of a company independently has the same probability of<br>being accident-free this year.<br><br>The expected number of accident-free employees is 9.<br><br>Calculate the variance of the number of accident-free employees this year.<br><br>A) 0.75<br>B) 1.50<br>C) 2.25<br>D) 9.00<br>E) 12.00", "tags": ["ExamP::UnivariateRV", "ExamP::UnivariateRV::ExpectationVariance"]},
