    {"back": "<b>Answer: B) 15</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>Let l = number of low-risk employees; therefore, there are 76 \u2013 l high-risk employees.<br>For independent random variables, the variance of the sum equals the sum of the variances.<br>Therefore:<br>2<br>22<br>43 1849 Var[Total # of Accidents]<br>Var[# of Accidents of Low Risk Ee] (76- ) Var[# of Accidents of High Risk Ee]<br>(0.50) (76 )(5.50)<br>2299 30<br>450 30<br>15.<br>ll<br>ll<br>l<br>l<br>l<br>= =<br>= \u00d7 +\u00d7<br>= +\u2212<br>= \u2212<br>=<br>=<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q542. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "Each of the 76 employees of a company is either a low-risk or a high-risk employee.<br>This year, each low-risk employee\u2019s number of accidents has standard deviation 0.50 and<br>each high-risk employee\u2019s number of accidents has standard deviation 5.50. The<br>standard deviation of the total number of accidents for all the employees is 43.00. The<br>frequencies of accidents among the employees are independent.<br><br>Calculate the number of low-risk employees.<br><br>A) 1<br>B) 15<br>C) 38<br>D) 61<br>E) 75", "tags": ["ExamP::GeneralProbability", "ExamP::GeneralProbability::Independence"]},
    {"back": "<b>Answer: B) p<br>2v</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>Let X represent the reported loss; note that X always exceeds d and Var[X] = v.<br>The claim payment is p(X - d) since X always exceeds d.<br><br>Var[claim payment] = Var[p(X - d)] = p<br>2Var[X \u2013 d] = p2Var[X] = p2v.<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q543. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "A renter\u2019s insurance policy pays a percentage p of the amount by which each loss<br>exceeds a deductible d. Each policyholder reports a loss if and only if the loss exceeds<br>the deductible.<br><br>The variance of a reported loss is v.<br><br>Determine the variance of the claim payment resulting from a reported loss.<br><br>A) pv<br>B) p<br>2v<br>C) p(v \u2013 d)<br>D) p2(v \u2013 d)<br>E) (1 \u2013 p)2v", "tags": ["ExamP::UnivariateRV", "ExamP::UnivariateRV::ExpectationVariance"]},
