    {"back": "<b>Answer: B) 0.08</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>Let X = number of accidents, which is binomial with \u201csuccess\u201d probability 0.3 and 4 trials. We<br>want to find<br>P[ 2].X &gt;<br><br>4<br>43 4<br>3<br>4P[ 2] (0.3) (0.7) 4(0.3) (0.7) (0.3) 0.0837.kk<br>k<br>X k<br>\u2212<br>=<br>\uf8eb\uf8f6&gt;= = + =\uf8ec\uf8f7\uf8ed\uf8f8\u2211<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q551. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "A motorist makes four driving errors this year. Each error independently has probability<br>0.3 of resulting in an accident. The motorist\u2019s insurance company reimburses up to two<br>accidents due to the motorist\u2019s errors this year.<br><br>Calculate the probability that these four errors result in at least one unreimbursed<br>accident.<br><br>A) 0.03<br>B) 0.08<br>C) 0.24<br>D) 0.32<br>E) 0.41", "tags": ["ExamP::GeneralProbability"]},
    {"back": "<b>Answer: B) 0.2a + 0.8b</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>Since the lifetime has constant probability density in the interval [a, b], the 80<br>th percentile is 80%<br>of the way from a to b, which equals: 0.8( ) 0.8 0.8 0.2 0.8 .a b a aba ab+ \u2212= + \u2212 = +<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q552. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "The distribution of the lifetime in years of a certain brand of lawnmower is uniform on<br>the interval [a, b], where 0 &lt; a &lt; b.<br><br>Determine the 80<br>th percentile of the lifetime in years of this brand of lawnmower.<br><br>A) a + 0.8b<br>B) 0.2a + 0.8b<br>C) 0.8a + 0.2b<br>D) 0.8( b \u2013 a)<br>E) 0.8( b + a)", "tags": ["ExamP::UnivariateRV", "ExamP::UnivariateRV::ContinuousDistributions"]},
