    {"back": "<b>Answer: D) 2236</b><br><br><b>Published solution:</b><br>A single bulb\u2019s lifetime has a variance of 1,000,000 (for an exponential distribution the variance<br>is the square of the mean).<br>The variance of the sum of five independent light bulb\u2019s lifetimes is 5,000,000. The standard<br>deviation is the square root, 2,236.<br><br><span style=\"color:#888;font-size:12px\">SOA Exam P Sample Questions/Solutions, Q588. https://www.soa.org/globalassets/assets/files/edu/edu-exam-p-sample-quest.pdf</span>", "front": "The lifetimes of light bulbs are independent and exponentially distributed with common<br>mean 1000 hours. A lamp has a single bulb and is continuously on. Each light bulb is<br>replaced immediately after it burns out.<br><br>Calculate the standard deviation of the time, in hours, until the failure of the fifth bulb.<br><br>A) 71<br>B) 158<br>C) 1000<br>D) 2236<br>E) 5000", "tags": ["ExamP::UnivariateRV", "ExamP::UnivariateRV::ContinuousDistributions"]},
